Package: foundry-linux-retro-tools
Version: 1.0.4
Architecture: all
Maintainer: World Foundry <packages@worldfoundry.org>
Installed-Size: 8
Depends: mame, mame-tools, dasm, cc65, z80dasm, z80asm, radare2, binwalk, sox, binutils-m68k-linux-gnu, xa65, f9dasm, libvgm, vgmstream
Recommends: ghidra
Suggests: java-common
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://foundrylinux.org/
Description: arcade reverse-engineering and porting toolchain
 Tooling for porting classic arcade ROMs to the World Foundry engine:
 MAME (debugger + tools), 6502/Z80/68k/6809 disassemblers and assemblers,
 radare2, binwalk, sox (audio conversion), xa65 6502 cross-assembler,
 f9dasm 6800/6809/6309 disassembler, libvgm (vgm-player + vgm2wav for
 chip-register VGM playback and rendering), vgmstream-cli (100+ game audio
 formats decoded to WAV).
 .
 Recommends: ghidra (repackaged from upstream, not yet shipped from the
 Foundry APT repo).
